ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a very good broad survey of trends in therapeutic discovery, but don't expect too much in terms of a very deep understanding of each individual therapeutic. A very reasonable amount of work, and the final, though a bit ominous due to lack of information, did only requiring paying attention in class.
Great class - I read a lot and loved discussing the material with the other students.
The course is quite stimulating, but it requires a fairly strong background before one can hope to profit fully from it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I'm not a graduate student but I felt I got a lot of perspective on some topics that I had never explored before!!
The course gave context to the work going on in my lab and others, which will guide my research and thesis writing in the coming years.
